<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1058,1625]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,523,1346,1372]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species is polymorphic found in all regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1177,1346,1372]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in the phytogeographic domains of the Amazon, Caatinga, Cerrado, Atlantic Rainforest and Pantanal, in rocky environments, seasonal forests and highland swamps (
<bibRefCitation author="Escobar, N. A. G. &amp; Silva, E. D. &amp; Tozzi, A. M. G. A." box="[393,552,1418,1444]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" pagination="752 - 765" refId="ref15692" refString="Escobar, N. A. G., Silva, E. D. &amp; Tozzi, A. M. G. A. (2014) Sinopse das Caesalpinioideae (Leguminosae) na Serra do Japi, Sao Paulo, Brasil. Rodriguesia 65: 752 - 765. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 78602014653103" type="journal article" year="2014">Escobar 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Flora do Brasil" box="[563,799,1418,1444]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" refId="ref15971" refString="Flora do Brasil 2020 (2020) Fabaceae. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. [http: // reflora. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 115]" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry box="[664,731,1418,1444]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1058,1625]" box="[189,864,1454,1480]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,1454,1480]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers and fruits in October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,1452,1058,1625]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,483,1490,1516]" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moench" authorityYear="1794" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[483,740,1490,1516]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nictitans">
<emphasis box="[483,740,1490,1516]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Chamaecrista nictitans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the subshrub habit, pilose branches, axillary cymose inflorescence and sessile legume fruit. This genus had four species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Moench" authorityYear="1794" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[997,1258,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nictitans">
<emphasis box="[997,1258,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Chamaecrista nictitans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
morphologically more similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Vogel" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[319,558,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis box="[319,558,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Chamaecrista repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by multi-leaf leaves, but they are distinguished by sessile nectary and 30–32– leaflet leaves in 
<emphasis box="[319,471,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName box="[319,433,1599,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nictitns">C. nictitns</taxonomicName>
vs.
</emphasis>
stipulate nectary and 20–22–leaflet leaves in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. S. Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Vogel" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[984,1090,1599,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Chamaecrista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="repens">
<emphasis box="[984,1090,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">C. repens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
